Surprisingly great food, its a little pricey but the quality was great so it was worth it. If youre looking for something healthy and very tasty and are willing to spend 15$ on a create your own i would definitely go for it!
Love their build your own bowl option. My go to is the spicy garlic sauce. Everything tastes very fresh and the portions are good.

People are def over hyping this place. I can definitely see its appeal and why people return. It's quick and fresh. However it is not flavourful. I had the spicy garlic noodles sub pineapple for jalapeños. The noodles were cooked perfectly however there was ZERO SPICE ZERO GARLIC FLAVOUR. I even had to ask for salt. Additionally some of my food was not heated all the way through, namely my chicken. Then there's the vegetables, specifically the broccoli and bell peppers. The broccoli texture felt like it had been par boiled then cooked and reheated like 5 times and was super soft. Also there were no large florets. The bell pepper still tasted raw and just barely warmed. I would've appreciated crunchier broccoli and cooked but crunchy bell peppers. Lastly the portion is small if you're a decent eater you'll be hungry again. Although, the person I was with made their own bowl and it was double mine so maybe that's the play? In any case, I wouldn't dissuade anyone from going but don't know if I'd return without a reason.
The food is delicious but only found 4 shrimps and a couple pieces of bacon in my stir fry. I expected more for the price I paid.
Stopped here on my 4 mile walk to the heart of Boston and I needed to refuel. This was so good even on the cold day. They have many locations around the city and I would recommend any of them!
Great Honeybar treat. Ready when expected, and delivered to us outside super easily -- COVID mandates and all.
You’ll enjoy designing a stir fry dish of your own at Honeygrow once you get a visit or two under your belt.   Delicious and a unique place, wish there was one in my town!
A lot of flavors, but they meshed well together.

Honeygrow has been a source of joy during the pandemic. Their spinach noodles matched with their spicy garlic sauce is a combination everyone should try at least once. Then the fact that tofu is an option is the cherry on top. Thank you for the fantastic service and delicious food.
Delicious noodle bowls!
Great food... I loved the red coconut curry with shrimp. Also the honeybar dessert! Yummy 🤩

If you have food allergies, do not eat or order from here. We ordered three dishes and specifically requested to avoid certain allergens. All three orders arrived incorrectly, and included the allergen we specifically ordered to avoid. Absolutely unacceptable and dangerous.  EDIT: I spoke with the regional manager and she urged us to give them a second chance, so we did. She advised us to specifically tell her (via her personal cell phone) when we were ordering again so she could assure our order would be correct.  It was not; once again, they got all three orders wrong - both chicken dishes had no chicken, and all three dishes contained several ingredients not requested.  I really must urge anyone with food allergies or dietary restrictions to avoid this restaurant, as even under the regional manager's direct supervision, they still cannot get your order right.

All these other reviews are underselling it. This place is FIRE! don't let anyone tell you different. That Walnut St. Noodle salad will make you want to roll your shoulders and give thanks. Some of the best food I've ever had in Boston. Don't play yourself, let Honeygrow into your life.

I'm giving HG 2 stars because the food is delicious. However, I noticed with the stir fries only about 1/3 cup total of add ins are in the meal. The rest is all noodles. Pre-defined or custom made bowls.   No prices online or wall menu.  You order at a touch screen kiosk.  We did all custom bowls... build one, then you get an option to add more.  Having not been through the screens it took a while. I am glad nobody was waiting behind us.  I assume they have an app where you can just re-order the bowl combination you like and go right to pickup.  The kiosk has a card scanner where you pay and get a very itemized receipt with all the items selected for each custom bowl.  In the custom menu you get to pick a set quantity of items in each category.  There is some base quantity of items you can get in each category.  You seam to know when you have hit the quantity of toppings when things you have not selected have an add-on price added.  Maybe there was a counter i did not see.  Vegan was a successful custom bowl build in our set.  Two bowls with rice noodles and one with whole wheat.  Everyone felt the pasta was a little under cooked as it felt a little firm.  Ingredients were fresh and had good flavor.  We ordered two bowls with the sauce on the side... their multi-spice topping.  In the end we found the sauces to our taste and if we ever visit one again we would just have them mix it in.  We would eat here again.

Good food fast. Loved ease of using the ordering kiosks to customize order. My only complaint is that some of the recipes/ingredients need some fine tuning. For example the crabmeat was full of shells and fried shallots was mostly shallot skins. Tried the beef another time and was a bit tough. Other than that the rice noodles and veggies are on point!

The best part of honeygrow is the ability to customize your meal. Sesame Garlic and Spicy Garlic are our favourite sauces and by choosing red chilies flakes for toppings can make it hotter! Delicious, quick and satisfying.

Great place to get tasty and quick noodles!  You walk in, and the ambiance is clean, colorful but not over the top. A nice casual place to seat in and have lunch. You walk over to the kiosk and select what you want. If you're making your own stir fry bowl, you get to pick a protein (price varies per protein), a base, a sauce, three veggies, and two garnishes within the price of the bowl. You pay at the kiosk, get your order number and wait for them to call it out - usually 5-10 min. I think if you do takeout, it shows up on the cool billboard. The food is tasty and the sauces are delicious. My bowl usually is a veggie one with an egg (extra), we white noodles, mushrooms, bell peppers, edamame, roasted cashews and pickled cucumbers with the sesame garlic sauce. They also do seasonal bowls, which is a nice change if you want to try something new. Someone also stopped by during our lunch to see if everything was alright, and that's just great customer service unexpected at a fast, casual restaurant.  Cons: 1. Since you select everything at the kiosk, you can't adjust the quantity. Say you want onions but just a little. Or you like mushrooms, so you would want more of it. 2. They're a little skimpy with the garnishes. I want more pickled cucumbers! 3. No steel forks even if you dine in. 4. I did enter my phone number but I'm not sure if I got any rewards for my order? 5. There's street parking but it can be tough on the weekends. 6. My biggest peeve was that the stir fry was cold for my liking, even though I ate in.  Overall, the flavors are good, and that deserves 4 stars!

The service is great and the food was good enough but it's way too expensive for a simple tossed together bowl of noodles or honey and yogurt - especially when the serving size isn't even that big. The space isnt especially welcoming either. Honestly, I probably won't go back again.

Find you a little Mom and Pop shop somewhere in town and save your coins for something better. Don't bother with their juices, either. Odd flavors and packed full of sugar. This place in general is one you can feel good about skipping over.  Service was 10/10. Efficient, nice, mindful. That's the only redeeming thing, though.
